ity or molecular crowding upon membrane bending. These results\nsuggest inherent CTxB-induced membrane bending as a mechanism for initiating\nCTxB internalization in cells that is initially independent of clathrin,\ncaveolin, actin, and lipid phase separation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 26 Mar 2017 20:04:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 30 Mar 2017 04:15:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-03-31"}
